title: Replies to initial written questions raised by Finance Committee Members in examining the Estimates of Expenditure 2010-11
question_text: Please list respectively the names of buildings where roof greening is either in progress or has been completed and the names of buildings where green building features have been incorporated. What is the manpower involved?
reply_text: A full list of government buildings where roof greening is either in progress or has been completed is at Annex A. Starting from 1999, green building features have been installed in existing government buildings whenever there are refurbishment and renovation projects. We believe a large number of government buildings have some green building features. However, a full list of government buildings with green building features is not available. At Annex B is a list of existing government buildings covered by projects approved in 2009-10 for implementing green building features. As these greening projects are undertaken by in-house staff who also handle other projects under the purview of the ArchSD, a separate breakdown of manpower required for these greening projects is not available.
